    "exam": "CDS (2) 2025",
    "question": "A car travels a total distance L. It travels half the distance with speed v1 and the other half with speed v2. The average speed of the car is:",
    "options": [
      "A. (v1 + v2) / 2",
      "B. 2v1v2 / (v1 + v2)",
      "C. (v1 + v2)L / 2v1v2",
      "D. L / (v1 + v2)"
    ],
    "answer": "B. 2v1v2 / (v1 + v2)",
    "explanation": "Average speed = Total Distance / Total Time. Time for first half = (L/2)/v1. Time for second half = (L/2)/v2. Total Time = L/2 * (1/v1 + 1/v2) = L/2 * (v1+v2)/(v1v2). Avg Speed = L / [L(v1+v2)/(2v1v2)] = 2v1v2/(v1+v2)."
