    "topic": "Geometry",
    "exam": "CISF 2021",
    "question": "Consider a square of side length 2 m. What is the difference of the areas of the circumscribed circle and the inscribed circle (in m²)?",
    "options": [
      "(a) 3п/2",
      "(b) 1/2",
      "(c) 2",
      "(d) п"
    ],
    "answer": "(d) п",
    "explanation": "Side = 2. Inscribed radius = 1, Area = pi * 1^2 = pi. Circumscribed radius = diagonal/2 = (2*sqrt(2))/2 = sqrt(2). Area = pi * (sqrt(2))^2 = 2pi. Difference = 2pi - pi = pi."
