    "question": "If first March of a year is Sunday, which day will be the first February of the next year?",
    "options": [
      "(a) Friday",
      "(b) Tuesday",
      "(c) Saturday",
      "(d) Monday"
    ],
    "answer": "(d) Monday",
    "explanation": "From March 1st to next year February 1st is 11 months. Total days = 31 (Mar) + 30 (Apr) + 31 (May) + 30 (Jun) + 31 (Jul) + 31 (Aug) + 30 (Sep) + 31 (Oct) + 30 (Nov) + 31 (Dec) + 31 (Jan) = 337 days. 337 / 7 = 48 weeks and 1 odd day. Sunday + 1 day = Monday."
